lab
===

Personal Linux systems toolbox. Learning experiment, also running in production
at home. Reads from /proc directly - no wrappers, no abstractions over
abstractions.

Tools
-----

  cktop    - terminal UI for system monitoring
  ckstat   - one-shot CLI, prints current memory usage
  ckagent  - metrics agent, exposes /proc data in Prometheus exposition format


cktop
-----

  go install github.com/ckinan/lab/cmd/cktop@latest


ckstat
------

  go install github.com/ckinan/lab/cmd/ckstat@latest

  ckstat          # human-readable
  ckstat -o json  # JSON


ckagent
-------

  go install github.com/ckinan/lab/cmd/ckagent@latest

  ckagent                  # listens on :9110
  ckagent -addr :9111      # custom port

Metrics at http://localhost:9110/metrics. Scrape with VictoriaMetrics or
Prometheus. Systemd unit and alert rules in deploy/.

Metrics exposed:

  cpu, memory, swap, load averages
  per-core CPU usage
  disk I/O (reads, writes, io time)
  network (bytes, packets, drops, errors per interface)
  open file descriptors
  socket counts (tcp, udp, raw, orphan, timewait)
  vmstat (page faults, paging, swapping)
  process/task counts
  system uptime
  apt last update and last upgrade timestamps
  PSI - pressure stall information (cpu, memory, io) system-wide and per-service
  per-service: CPU %, RSS, process count, PSI (via cgroups)


Development
-----------

Requires Go 1.21+ and Task (taskfile.dev).

  task build          # build all binaries
  task test           # unit tests
  task run:agent      # run ckagent locally
  task install:agent  # build and deploy to /usr/local/bin + restart systemd unit

